1. Copy the example configuration file (ghbakrc.example) to one of the
   following locatons:
     ~/.ghbakrc
	 /etc/ghbak.rc
	 ./ghbak.rc
2. Update the new configuration file with the location to store the backup
   of your repositories (BACKUP_DIR) and your GitHub username (GITHUB_USER).
   Optionally, add a space separated list of repositories to skip (EXCLUDE).
3. Set a cronjob to execute the 'ghbak.sh' script hourly/daily/whatever.
